captions.text:
[MUSIC CHARITY VANCE, "TWO
 BIRDS"]
-Hi, we're Brooklyn and Bailey.

And today, we're kind of
doing a special video.

We're interviewing our
parents, because they
got to go on set for the new--
-"Catching Fire--"
- --movie.

And they had lots of fun, so
we're just interviewing them.

We're asking them questions and
stuff about their experience.
So let's go see it.
Who is Linda Flowers?

-So Linda Flowers is
the head hair stylist

for all of the
"Hunger Games" movies.
-That sounds cool.
-Yes.

-So how are you and
Linda Flowers connected?
Like, where did that all happen?

-OK, so she originally
saw our Katniss

braid on YouTube after the first
movie and got in touch with us.
And we started connecting.

And then, when she was
filming the second movie,

she contacted us
again and let us

know that she had used one of
our hairstyles in the movie,

and then invited us to
come and be on set one day.

So that's how all
that connected.

-So how did you get onto
the set of "Catching Fire"?
-It was kind of crazy.

So Linda brought Mindy and
I on kind of as consultants.

So we get there,
and she hands me

a bag, a clear bag of make
up with hair stuff in it.

And then, she has
a backpack for me

that I had to carry
around as a hair guy.
But it was so awkward, you know?

Because I was always
afraid a star was

going to come and be
like, hey, can you
fix this hair over here?
And I don't know what to do!

I'm just a camera guy on Cute
Girls Hairstyles, you know?

So she brought us on kind of as
a consultant to get us on set.

-What stars did you
get to meet on the set?
-Ooh, all the good ones!

We met Josh, and
Jen, and I think

we were there the
day that they were
filming the chariot scenes.
So all the tributes were there.

So we were actually kind of
sitting right by the tributes

and hanging out
with a lot of them.

We did not get to
meet Haymitch or Prim.
-Oh!

-Because they weren't
filming that day.
Kind of a bummer.

-Did you have a
favorite tribute?
-I really liked Josh!
He's so nice in real life.
-Really?
-Yes!
He's just as nice in real life.
I swear, he was really nice.

-Did you meet any
of the characters
from the set on "Catching Fire"?

-That day, we met
pretty much all of them.
In fact, we had lunch with them.

And we didn't know
who the tributes were.

So we're sitting
there at the table,

and they're all kind of looking
at us like, who are you?

And we're looking at
them like, well, they're
dressed up really cool.

So they must be in the
movie, because we had lunch

before we actually
started filming.

And then, at one point
after the chariot scene,

actually in the middle
of the chariot scene,
I was getting a little hungry.

And so I asked Linda and
Mindy if they wanted anything.

So I went over to
the catering table.

And it was just
picking some stuff up.

And then, there was
a tap on my shoulder.

And I turned around, and
it's Josh Hutcherson, Peeta.
Peeta was there.

And he was like, you
don't belong here, do you?
I'm like, how'd you guess?

He's like, well,
hair and make up?

You just don't look like the
hair and make up kind of guy.
I'm like, well, I'm not.
We're here visiting with Linda.

My wife is helping her on
some of the hair styles.
He said, oh!
That's really cool.

He's popping-- he
was eating nuts.

He wasn't eating
anything unhealthy.
He was eating nuts.
But he introduced himself.
He's like, hi, I'm Josh.
We shake hands.

And I'm like, yeah, we
pretty much know who you are.
So that was pretty cool.
-Did you get to meet Katniss?
-Yes, we did.
Only just for a few minutes.

After they come off set,
they go into the trailer.

And they have all their
hair and makeup taken off.

Because they obviously
can't wear it off
set for people to see.

And so when she came back into
the hair and make up trailer,
we were in there.

And when she was
having it taken off,

we got to visit with
her for a few minutes
and ask her a few questions.

And she was talking
about her cat.

And they took off- it
was the chariot scene.

So she had a lot of
fake hair and some wigs

and some head pieces
that were on her hair.
So they were taking them off.

And as Linda was
taking them off,
she was handing them to me.
I'm like, OK!

I'll just stand here and
hold Jen's head piece, OK.
It was so crazy!

-Were there any
funny moments on set

that you just thought were
hysterical or something?
-Yes, there was one.

So the day we were there, they
were filming the chariot scene.
I already said that.

So they were all in their
big, beautiful costumes.

And you did not get to see
this in the movie because they

didn't really show the costumes
that the other tributes were
wearing, the other victors.

But they were amazing,
amazing, amazing costumes.

And the girl that plays Joanna
had on this amazing tree
outfit.

And it was this super skin-tight
unitards with this bodice part.
She looked amazing in it.
And she had this fantastic body.

And she had on heels
seriously like this big.
They were crazy.

And every time she
would walk across set,

everybody's heads
would go like this.

Because the outfit, the
shoes, her body, everything,
she looked fantastic.

And so at one point,
her phone rings.

And she trying to back away
from where they were filming off

in the distance so that
she wouldn't be noisy.

And Dad happened to be
sitting in a director's chair,
so was sitting down kind of low.

And he was leaning like
this, watching them film.

And she came and stood
right in front of him.

So her butt is
right in his face.
And he's like this.
And here's her fanny.

And he's like-- and
everyone's looking over

and just snickering,
because he's

like-- how can you not be
staring right at her derriere
when it's right there?
It was just so funny?
And he looks at me.
And he just looks at her butt.
And he's like, what do I do?
Because it's right there.
It was so funny, so funny.
Great body.
Way to go, Joanna.

-Where there any funny
moments on set that you saw?

-Actually, the characters
were having a lot of fun
once they cut the filming.

In fact, I remember
in the chariot scene

when Katniss and Peeta
are with the horses

and getting ready to go
into the capital stadium,

when they were cutting the shot,
Peeta and Katniss were having

armpit fart contests,
where they lick their palm
and go like this, you know?

And it was so funny, because
the director's saying,
we're getting ready to roll!

And they would get right
back into character.

-It's funny because it's such
a serious part of the movie.
-Oh, yeah.

And as soon as they were on cut,
they were right back doing it.
It was really funny.

In fact, you can
probably see red armpits
on Katniss in the movie.

-What was your favorite
part about being on set?

-I think just
getting to be there.

Just getting to
have the opportunity

to be there, to see everything,
see all the costumes
and the hair.
Nobody gets to do that.

It was like this
top secret place.

We weren't even allowed to
know where it was until the day
before.

They didn't even
send us the address.
It was so, so top secret.

They wouldn't let us bring
any kind of electronic stuff
with us.
No phone, nothing.

So we couldn't
take any pictures.

So I think just the fact that
I have that memory in my brain
is so cool.
That's my favorite part.
Thank you, Linda!

-What are the names of
the hair styles that

are in the "Catching
Fire" movie?

-So the one that she
used was the bow braid.

But we saw lots of
variations of hair styles
that we've done on our channel.

We saw a variation
of the bun hawk.

We saw a variation of
twist back flip under.
I'm trying to think.
There were so many, so many.

I can't remember
even all of them,

but they were
amazing, all the hair.

She uses a lot of wigs for
a lot of-- obviously, Effie.

But there's a lot of extra
hair and extensions and wigs
and that kind of stuff.

So a lot of them were souped
up versions of our hairstyles.
But they were just amazing.

I mean, I could've sat there
and stared at their hair all day
long.

-While our parents were on
set, they got a "Catching Fire"
book signed by--

-Haymitch, Peeta, Katniss,
and Finnick, all of them.
Signed!

-And my parents are having
a giveaway on their channel.
It's the--
-Prim Bow Braid Tutorial--
-Video.

-Just click the link below
if you want to enter and win

a signed copy of
"Catching Fire."

-Make sure you leave a comment
below on your favorite part

in the new "Catching
Fire" movie.

And we'll see you
guys next week.
[KISS]
[WHISTLING]

[MUSIC CHARITY VANCE, "TWO
 BIRDS"]
-[INAUDIBLE].
-Don't [INAUDIBLE].
And I didn't reach the note.
I was like--

-You're going too
slow on the thing.
[WHISTLING]
-I can't reach the high note.
-Ah.
This one's hard.
-You can barely whistle.
